videos.title: Meet the Trainers
videos.description: Learn more about Amy Johnston, Caitlin Dechelle, Anisha Gibbs, Michelle Jubilee, Thekla Hutyrova and Corinne van Ryck de Groot

videos.title: Karate Kardio
videos.description: Kick your calorie-burning into high gear with martial arts-inspired cardio intervals designed to maximize fat loss, build coordination, and boost athleticism.

videos.title: Booty Building Boxing
videos.description: Alternate between boxing combos and butt-sculpting moves like squats and lunges to get fighting fit—and a firmer booty.

videos.title: Superhero Cardio
videos.description: This intense cardio meltdown will leave you feeling like a superhero. Fight your way through the main workout using kicks and punches you’ve seen in the movies, then attack the burnout at the end to torch even more fat.

videos.title: Street Dance Cardio
videos.description: Let loose, have fun, and burn tons of calories with this dance-based cardio routine set to jazz-funk and Afrobeats.

videos.title: Burn Like a Boss
videos.description: Grab a pair of dumbbells and prepare to sweat your way to a leaner, more defined body with fast-paced circuits that shift your calorie-burn into overdrive.

videos.title: MMA Dance Cardio
videos.description: This kick-ass dance routine is just what you need to become a lean, mean fighting machine.

videos.title: Total Body Killer Core
videos.description: You’ll feel the burn in your legs, chest, back, and arms as you sweat through four rounds of exercises designed to build strength, torch fat, and carve head-turning abs.

videos.title: HIIT It
videos.description: You don’t need weights for this fast-paced workout, but don’t let that fool you—your body weight provides all of the resistance you need to build muscle, burn fat, and work up a killer sweat.

videos.title: HIIT Where It Counts
videos.description: You’ll need dumbbells and a fun-loving attitude to complete this heart-pounding, muscle-burning, fat-incinerating HIIT workout.

videos.title: Fight Fit
videos.description: The MMA-inspired bodyweight exercises in this circuit-training workout will help you build the lean, shredded body of pro fighter.

videos.title: Power Resistance
videos.description: A combination of plyometric, martial arts, and classic strength-training moves will help you build muscle and explosive power from head to toe.

videos.title: Total Body Shred
videos.description: You’ll need to dig deep to finish this intense, total-body resistance workout designed to increase strength, power, and definition all over.

videos.title: Core Incinerator
videos.description: Hold nothing back during this intense, core-shredding routine. If your abs aren’t begging for mercy by the time you’re done, you didn’t push yourself hard enough.

videos.title: Karate Core
videos.description: You’ll hammer every muscle in your core as you fight to maintain your balance and stability during muscle-burning kicks, punches, and static holds.

videos.title: COREdio
videos.description: You’ll alternate between core work and high-intensity cardio in this ab-sculpting, fat-incinerating, total-body workout that’s sure to make you sweat.

videos.title: Revive and Restore
videos.description: A series of static and dynamic stretches will help you ease muscle tension, increase blood flow, and enhance total-body mobility for a faster, more complete recovery.

videos.title: Fight Flow
videos.description: This relaxing recovery session uses a combination of yoga, qi gong, and martial arts to help refresh your body and mind.

videos.title: 6 Kicks You Should Know
videos.description: Breakdown of the fundamental kicks: Front Kick, Side Kick, Back Kick, Round Kick, Hook Kick, and Crescent Kick.

videos.title: 8 Punches You Should Know
videos.description: Breakdown of the fundamental punches: Jab, Cross, Hook, Uppercut, Up Elbow, Side Elbow, Downward Elbow, and Superman Punch.

videos.title: 3 Stances You Should Know
videos.description: Breakdown of the fundamental martial arts stances: Horse Stance, Fight Stance, and Boxing Stance.

videos.title: Advanced Moves to Master
videos.description: Breakdown of some advanced moves: Triple-Threat Elbow, Slip Hook Superman Punch, Defense Combo, Power Pop Up, The Getaway and Jab and Weave.

videos.title: Welcome to T-MINUS 30
videos.description: Hunter welcomes you to the program, takes you on a tour of what’s inside, and lets you know what to expect during the next 30 days on your journey to the starting line!

videos.title: Meet Hunter
videos.description: Meet Hunter, your coach, trainer, and teammate for the next 30 days. He shares his incredible story and gives you a taste of what it takes to be a four-time TOUGH MUDDER champion.

videos.title: Extreme Conditioning 1.0
videos.description: This is where it all begins—with a sweaty, bodyweight circuit that uses high-intensity cardio intervals to build power and endurance.

videos.title: Dumbbell Endurance 1.0
videos.description: Grab a set of weights and get ready to work! Today, Hunter focuses on building upper-body strength and stamina to make sure you’re tough enough to conquer any obstacle on the course.

videos.title: Athletic Training Day 1.0
videos.description: Hunter trains you to perform like an athlete with explosive cardio and bodyweight conditioning designed to help you tackle any TOUGH MUDDER course.

videos.title: Dynamic Dumbbells 1.0
videos.description: Back to dumbbells, but today’s workout emphasizes a split-leg stance to build balance and total-body strength—and to carve your abs. You can thank Hunter later.

videos.title: Mudder Ground Strength 1.0
videos.description: To crush the toughest obstacles, you need to get down and dirty, staying low and using your core. That’s what this workout trains you to do. You’ll feel like you’re already on the course with Hunter.

videos.title: Mudder Mobility
videos.description: Stretch tired muscles and release tension throughout your body as you enhance mobility and unlock greater strength and power. Enjoy this relaxing recovery session. You earned it.

videos.title: Extreme Conditioning 2.0
videos.description: Hunter ups the challenge from last week’s workout by adding more high-intensity cardio and bodyweight training that will test your stamina and grit. You got this.

videos.title: Dumbbell Endurance 2.0
videos.description: This week, Hunter works you harder with tougher moves and more reps. His goal: giving you the power to conquer any obstacle by maximizing your upper-body and grip strength.

videos.title: Athletic Training Day 2.0
videos.description: Get ready for Hunter to “mess” with you by switching things up with more explosive cardio and more challenging bodyweight moves. Trust us, the payoff—a fitter, leaner, more athletic body—is worth it.

videos.title: Dynamic Dumbbells 2.0
videos.description: Grab your weights and get your mind right, because during the next 30 minutes, Hunter will push you harder than ever. By the time you’re done, there won’t be a single muscle not shaking.

videos.title: Mudder Ground Strength 2.0
videos.description: It’s time to get grounded again. Hit the deck to work your core as you train your body to overcome the most mind-bending obstacles you’ll face on the course.

videos.title: Mudder Mobility
videos.description: Stretch tired muscles and release tension throughout your body as you enhance mobility and unlock greater strength and power. Enjoy this relaxing recovery session. You earned it.

videos.title: Extreme Conditioning 3.0
videos.description: By now, you should feel fit enough to tackle this intense interval session without hitting pause. But be forewarned: Hunter packed this week’s workout with sick new moves that will push your limits.

videos.title: Dumbbell Endurance 3.0
videos.description: We hope you’re feeling rested, because Hunter is looking to crush you with new dumbbell progressions that will increase your muscular strength and endurance—if you can handle them.

videos.title: Athletic Training Day 3.0
videos.description: Expect some new twists in this workout as Hunter shares more elite training techniques that will take your fitness and athleticism to new heights.

videos.title: Dynamic Dumbbells 3.0
videos.description: More reps, heavier weights, harder moves—Hunter is determined to maximize your gains, so don’t hold back. Your muscles will be burning by the time you’re done, but it will all be worth it on race day.

videos.title: Mudder Ground Strength 3.0
videos.description: You’ll feel like you’re on the course as you mimic ducking under barbed wire and scrambling through tunnels, but your core will be tight and TOUGH MUDDER-ready when it comes time to do it for real.

videos.title: Mudder Mobility
videos.description: Stretch tired muscles and release tension throughout your body as you enhance mobility and unlock greater strength and power. Enjoy this relaxing recovery session. You earned it.

videos.title: Total Body Challenge
videos.description: Three simple moves have never felt so hard and yet…so good.

videos.title: The 300 Challenge
videos.description: 300 reps, that is. Or is it 360? Hunter might have lied :)

videos.title: Obstacle Day Challenge
videos.description: Five rounds of five moves with no rest equal a cold, hard challenge to your body and your mind—a challenge that will help prepare you to crush any TOUGH MUDDER course, no matter the distance.

videos.title: Reps Win Races
videos.description: Pick up your weights—and get ready to hold them until the end. Oh, yes, this one is going to burn.

videos.title: Sheriff Abs
videos.description: Hunter calls it a quick 15 minutes of ab and core training. You might not think it’s quite quick enough. Either way, this will become a go-to abs routine for you.

videos.title: Burpee Challenge
videos.description: Yep, it’s exactly what it sounds like. We could have called it Death by Burpees—but would that make you feel any better?

videos.title: Intro to Upper-Body Grip Strength
videos.description: Hunter explains why chin-up and pull-up training will become your best friends while prepping for a TOUGH MUDDER—even if you’ve never done a single chin-up or pull-up before.

videos.title: Chin-Up Training
videos.description: This quick, 15-minute workout shows you how to perform the chin-up with proper form and runs you through the first week’s routine for the 5K and the Classic.

videos.title: Pull-Up Training
videos.description: This quick, 15-minute workout shows you how to perform the pull-up with proper form and runs you through the first week’s routine for the 5K and the Classic.

videos.title: Intro to Run Training
videos.description: Hunter explains the importance of running in addition to your T-MINUS 30 workouts for taking on a TOUGH MUDDER.

videos.title: Short Interval Run (Audio Only)
videos.description: Hunter coaches you through one of his favorite running workouts, which alternates one minute of sprinting with one minute of walking. See the training guide for complete run training programs.

videos.title: Long Interval Run (Audio Only)
videos.description: Join Hunter to build your endurance with longer intervals that alternate five minutes of intense running and two minutes of jogging. See the training guide for complete run training programs.

videos.title: Recovery Run (Audio Only)
videos.description: Running with Hunter is better than running alone. Hunter guides you through a 45-minute run with intervals, stretching, and motivational tips to help you build your endurance and confidence. See the training guide for complete run training programs.

videos.title: Intro to Taper Week
videos.description: Hunter takes you through taper week (the week of your event). Learn how to adjust your workouts to maintain your gains while preparing your body to perform at its peak on race day.

videos.description: Hunter explains Everest, Funky Monkey, Block-ness Monster, Kiss of Mud, and Berlin Walls, along with his pro tips to conquer them.
